<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1743" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1743">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 718.1915/223.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Minister of Costa
                                    Rica</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-16">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 16, 1914</hi></date>,</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of November 7, in which, in compliance with special
                            instructions from your Government, you express its gratitude for the
                            mediation of the Chief Justice of the United States, a copy of whose
                            award you enclose, in the boundary dispute between Costa Rica and
                            Panama.</p>
                        <pb facs="1132" n="1016" xml:id="pg_1016"/>
                        <p>In reply I beg to assure you of the profound gratification with which the
                            Department has learned of your Government’s satisfaction with the
                            results of the friendly good offices which it afforded pleasure to the
                            Government of the United States to extend to the Governments of Costa
                            Rica and Panama in this matter.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>